&lt;p&gt;Senior Infection Prevention Control Nurse – Band 8A&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are delighted to offer this substantive post and opportunity for an experienced, motivated, and enthusiastic person with leadership skills, to join our team. The role requires application of a wide range of expert skills, knowledge, and guidance for delivery across our health and social care system. In addition, we work alongside our regional Infection Prevention Control colleagues and across our own Cambridgeshire and Peterborough system in our Operational Group, linking to our IPC Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Application closure: Sunday 8th November Planned interview date: Monday 16th November 2020 via Microsoft Teams For further details or information please contact Lynn Rodrigues, Consultant Nurse Infection Prevention Control on 07983 159898 or email lynn.rodrigues@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that the CCG is currently working through a period of change regarding Ways of Working and it is likely that on appointment into this role the successful candidate will be required to work a mixture of their working days between their home, stakeholder locations across Cambridgeshireand a new office location planned in Ely, Cambs. The ability to attend locations throughout the Cambridgeshire and Peterborough geography will be essential for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
